theorem Topology.closure_eq_closure_interior_closure_interior_of_P2
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 A → closure A = closure (interior (closure (interior A))) := by
  intro hP2
  -- Step 1: `P2` yields `closure A = closure (interior A)`.
  have h₁ := Topology.closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P2 (X := X) (A := A) hP2
  -- Step 2: Use the idempotent property of `closure ∘ interior`
  -- to rewrite `closure (interior A)`.
  have h₂ :=
    (Topology.closure_interior_closure_interior_eq_closure_interior
        (X := X) (A := A)).symm
  -- Step 3: Combine the two equalities.
  simpa [h₂] using h₁
